    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="875"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-01T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 1, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>136. Referring to the last paragraph of article 4 of the proposed treaty the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs today suggested to me that I endeavor to arrange a
                    conference at the Legation in Panama between Drs. Alfaro and Garay and
                    representative officers from the Panama Canal.</p>
                <p>The Governor tells me that of the officers of the Panama Canal best informed on
                    this subject; namely, the Executive Secretary, the Counsel, and Chief of Police,
                    the first and last are on leave and the second departs on leave tomorrow. The
                    Governor, however, will have a complete memorandum prepared for each conference
                    or conferences, if any take place.</p>
                <p>Inasmuch as Drs. Alfaro and Garay expect to sail for the United States next week
                    the Department’s telegraphic instruction as to whether to hold conversations on
                    this subject at the Legation are requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
